title: Unlocking the Health Benefits of Nature
description:
How does being close to nature improve your health and well-being? In Shetland and beyond, doctors have taken to prescribing time in nature for patients.

A lecture by Jacqueline McGlade, Frank Jackson Foundation Professor of the Environment
12 November 2019 6PM GMT
https://www.gresham.ac.uk/lectures-and-events/reconnecting-with-nature

Nature’s benefits to human health are so well-attested, that the medical profession is now actively engaged in fighting for a clean, healthy environment as a human right and prescribing it as treatment across the world from Shetland to Japan. So how does being close to nature improve your health and well-being and how can this help us achieve UN Sustainable Development Goal 3 to "ensure healthy lives and promote wellbeing for all at all ages”?
